  "text": "The ext_authz filter in Envoy (v1.31.2) implements external authorization through both HTTP and network filters. The implementation contains three key security control mechanisms:\n\n## 1. Per-Route Bypass Configuration\n\nThe bypass/passthrough logic is implemented in the HTTP filter (`source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.h` and `.cc`):\n\n- **FilterConfigPerRoute class** (ext_authz.h:231-273): Defines per-route configuration with a `disabled()` method that returns whether the ext_authz check should be skipped for a specific route.\n\n- **getPerRouteFlags() function** (ext_authz.cc:810-827): Retrieves the most specific per-route configuration and extracts the `skip_check_` flag from the route's FilterConfigPerRoute.\n\n- **decodeHeaders() function** (ext_authz.cc:226-277): The entry point for HTTP request processing. It calls `getPerRouteFlags()` to determine if the current route has disabled ext_authz (line 228-229), and if so, returns immediately without calling the authorization service (lines 230-231).\n\nThe per-route configuration is loaded via the `ExtAuthzPerRoute` protobuf message which has a `disabled` field that can be set to `true` to bypass authorization for specific routes.\n\n## 2. Authorization Decision Caching and Route Cache Control\n\nWhile Envoy does not implement caching of authorization responses, it provides route cache clearing functionality:\n\n- **clearRouteCache flag** (ext_authz.h:73): A configuration option that controls whether Envoy should clear the route cache after authorization decisions.\n\n- **Route cache clearing logic** (ext_authz.cc:436-441): In the `onComplete()` function, when the authorization returns OK status and certain headers/query parameters are modified, the filter clears the route cache by calling `decoder_callbacks_->downstreamCallbacks()->clearRouteCache()`. This ensures that header/query parameter modifications from the authz server affect routing decisions.\n\n## 3. Immediate Response Path\n\nThe ext_authz filter provides several immediate response mechanisms (sendLocalReply) for denying access without forwarding to the upstream service:\n\n- **Disabled filter immediate response** (ext_authz.cc:234-244): When the ext_authz filter is disabled globally but `deny_at_disable` is configured, the filter sends a local reply with the configured error status code.\n\n- **Authorization denied immediate response** (ext_authz.cc:678-736): In `onComplete()`, when the authorization service returns a DENIED status, the filter immediately sends a local reply with the status code and body from the authorization response using `decoder_callbacks_->sendLocalReply()`.\n\n- **Authorization error immediate response** (ext_authz.cc:739-767): When the authorization service returns an ERROR status and `failure_mode_allow` is not configured, the filter sends a local reply with the configured error status.\n\n- **Invalid response rejection** (ext_authz.cc:771-784): The `rejectResponse()` function sends a local reply (HTTP 500) when the authorization response contains invalid headers or query parameters.\n\n## Supporting Implementation Files\n\n**gRPC Client** (`source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/ext_authz_grpc_impl.cc`):\n- `GrpcClientImpl::onSuccess()` (lines 106-144): Processes authorization responses from gRPC service\n- `GrpcClientImpl::onFailure()` (lines 146-156): Handles communication failures\n\n**HTTP Client** (`source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/ext_authz_http_impl.cc`):\n- `RawHttpClientImpl::toResponse()` (lines 318-398): Converts HTTP authorization responses into internal Response objects\n- Response status code (200 = OK, other = DENIED, 5xx = ERROR)\n\n**Network Filter** (`source/extensions/filters/network/ext_authz/ext_authz.cc`):\n- `Filter::onData()` (lines 40-53): TCP filter entry point with `filterEnabled()` check at line 41\n- `Filter::onComplete()` (lines 72-130): Handles authorization responses at network layer, closing connections on denied/error\n\n**Common Utilities** (`source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/check_request_utils.cc`):\n- Request creation and header matching logic for building CheckRequest messages\n\n## Configuration Registration\n\n- **HTTP Filter Config** (`source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/config.h`): Registers the ExtAuthzFilterConfig factory that creates ExtAuthzPerRoute per-route configurations\n- **Network Filter Config** (`source/extensions/filters/network/ext_authz/config.h`): Registers the network filter configuration factory\n"
}

